class.javadoc:
Constructs a new {@code UUID} using the specified data. {@codemostSigBits} is used for the most significant 64 bits of the {@codeUUID} and {@code leastSigBits} becomes the least significant 64 bits of the {@code UUID}.
mostSigBitsThe most significant bits of the {@code UUID}
leastSigBitsThe least significant bits of the {@code UUID}

Static factory to retrieve a type 3 (name based) {@code UUID} based on the specified byte array.
nameA byte array to be used to construct a {@code UUID}
A {@code UUID} generated from the specified array

Creates a {@code UUID} from the string standard representation as described in the {@link #toString} method.
nameA string that specifies a {@code UUID}
A {@code UUID} with the specified value
IllegalArgumentExceptionIf name does not conform to the string representation as described in {@link #toString}
